item.title: Visual Storyteller Bio Picture
item.dc:creator: davidianshaw
item.content:encoded: Challenge: To create a profile picture for my colleague Sarah Moyle. She is an amazing Visual Storyteller and wanted something that represented what she does. Solution: To highlight her brand, we put her in front of one of her wall sized visual stories. I wanted to capture her creativity as well and tie the background drawing to the potential customers looking for a visual storyteller. To reinforce the graphic facilitation message markers were strategically placed in her hands. Outcome: Sarah is an underground star in the world of visual storytelling. The profile picture has helped her communicate her expertise and her creative brand to the likes of the LEGO Serious Play community.

item.title: Intel Recruiting Video - Clem Cole
item.dc:creator: davidianshaw
item.content:encoded: [wpvideo EOoSJxle] Challenge: Intel knew it had something special with Clem Cole. What they didn't know was why the next generation of leaders flocked to him at recruiting events. As part of the Stanford Intel training program for VPs, Pat McDonald VP of Talent Management, was asked to do a deep dive on millennials and how we capture their interest. In addition, the team wanted to understand why a long-time employee was highly sought after at recruiting events. Solution: To create a profile video of Clem Cole, a seasoned technologist that was popular at recruiting events. We dove into some of the reasons why he was so popular and what he brought to this new generation of leaders. Outcome: The result was a profile video on Clem Cole, Intel HPC Architect and why we need the next generation of leaders here at Intel. It was used as part of talent marketing.

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: davidianshaw
item.content:encoded:
Questioning the status quo since 1969. Funny, but it's true. And it's my email signature. I’ve always known I was a bit different and saw things in a different light than most people. born outside of Philadelphia, I spent my first 14 years in suburbia. Although, I never felt like I fit in. From a young a ge I was always conscious about the world around me, the delicate balance that life existed in. I hated seeing trash all over the place. I wanted people to think about what happens to that wrapper that just got thrown on the ground. I didn't know it then, but I was well on the path to becoming some type of leader championing change for good- that our environment was our house and we were messing things up. A move from the east coast west to Portland Oregon changed everything. Talk about culture shock. At first it was really hard. But over time I realized that the west coast culture "fit" me.

My interest lies in human problems where I like to provoke and inspire individuals/teams to think differently. Sometimes solutions to problems need different approaches to make sense of complexity. I’m both a left-brain AND right-brain thinker and have experience coaching at all leadership levels, as well as mentoring junior team members. Over my career, I have worked across multiple business functions including R&D, Product, IT, and HR. I’ve been an artist since childhood and have a strong belief in serious play.

Ask me about the weather. The answer might surprise you.

item.title: Technical Leadership Pipeline Application
item.dc:creator: davidianshaw
item.content:encoded:
PROJECT OBJECTIVE

As part of the Data Center Group, I partnered with a business lead to help create a tool to manage the Technical Leader Pipeline. This project solved a few critical issues. First, the process was currently being done via email and excel. This led to multiple copies, data errors, and lastly data excursions with personal data.

For this project I rapidly learned Angular, built a prototype for testing, then reused the code for the front-end development. It saved weeks of development as well as roughly $20k for the cost of the upfront design.

ROLE(S)

Technical Program Manager
Interaction Designer Visual Designer
UI Developer

DURATION

9 Months

About Us

Our Beliefs

We believe in a world where every child can read. Our mission is to invest in early childhood education in order to empower the next generation. We do that, by creating educational programs and providing necessary resources in underprivileged areas. We believe in smart fund allocation, and therefore we employ minimal staff.

How You Can Help

Send Donation

Giving online has never been more secure, convenient or hassle-free with our one-click donation. We also do accept standard cash and check donations at all of our locations.

Become a Volunteer

You can get involved today by becoming a Volunteer. Sign up and you will be joining a group of change-makers, a network strong enough to impact positive change in the lives of children.

Your gift will help equip children in need with necessary resources, training and education while offering the promise of a brighter future. You can make a difference today by signing up.
